	   <tr><td colspan=2>Think of it this way (numbers listed are just an example)...<br><br>You have 24 points (locations)<br><br>At any given time, only 6 may be active...<br><br>Now you have 2 things that may be at that location...<br><br>The negative thing has a 90% chance at being there...<br>The positive thing has a 10% chance at being there...<br>Only 1 positive thing may be in the active locations...<br><br>After a certain duration (fixed or random) these locations become inactive and 6 of the 24 are randomly chosen to become active for the next round of triggers...<br><br>Personally, I have only seen 6 active spawn points at one time... sometimes I only see 4 active spawn points... so it is possible that the number of active spawns may be random, or it may be possible that I missed some, or they were too close to eachother for me to gague...<br><br>I recently helped someone out, in this portion... I found Tanik on the southern side of the Kael wall... 6 feet from a DS spawn point... I was using my Mage twink to triangulate his position and discovered the "You are too far away from You have to trade!" So I then triangulated the position of the DS... both Tanik and DS were too close to eachother for comfort... I parked my pet so he was facing the Tanik spawn point (You are too far away from You stumble to trade!), and called the guy over to spawn him.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ibiar Manavein<br>54 Erudite Wizard<br>-Vangurds of Excellence-<br>Erollisi Marr</td></tr>
